Subject: Pan-Pacific Association of Applied Linguistics 
 

Full Title: Pan-Pacific Association of Applied Linguistics 
Short Title: PAAL 

Date: 19-Dec-2007 - 21-Dec-2007
Location: Pattaya, Thailand 
Contact Person: Yusuke Kondo
Meeting Email: office@paaljapan.org
Web Site: http://paaljapan.org 

Linguistic Field(s): Applied Linguistics 

Call Deadline: 31-Aug-2007 

Meeting Description:

The PAAL Conference is a forum for academic exchange among scholars and
parishioners in applied linguistics and related areas. The conference provides a
venue for the dissemination of current research on a wide variety of issues
concerning Asia and beyond. 

Proposals: 

(1) Subscribe to PAAL member before submitting your proposal. 
(2) Submit your proposal on the website below (This site is available on Aug 1). 
http://paaljapan.org/conference2007/abst.html 
(3) Limit your proposal to 400 words or less. 
(4) The deadline of submission of proposals is Aug 31. 
(5) The notification of acceptance is expected to be sent by the end of Sep. 
Proceedings 
(1) The deadline of submission of proceedings is Oct 31. 
(2) Submit your paper on the website below (This site is available on Oct 1). 
http://paaljapan.org/conference2007/proc.html 
(3) Limit your paper to 2 or 4 page. 
(4) The template for PAAL proceedings is available on Oct 1.



	
